	(text "Power\nTest\nPoints"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 364.744 102.362 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "9d4ab40a-89db-4424-b86e-fa6fb11b6580")
	)
	(text "VCU Module TOP-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE\n\nThis page summarizes the VCU Module board, including power supply,\nSTM32 control, CAN-FD interface, I/O connectors, and debug/test access points.\n\n1. POWER\nJ3 receives the 7V-32V power input. BMU-POWER provides fuse protection, power switch,\nPMOS input protection, 7V-32V to 5 V conversion, 5 V to 3.3 V regulation, and\npower-status LEDs.\n\n2. MCU / DEBUG\nBMU-MCU contains the STM32 controller, reset circuit, STDC14 SWD connector,\nCAN control signals, reserved GPIO, and shutdown signal.\n\n3. CAN-FD\nBMU-CAN provides the MCP2562FD CAN-FD physical-layer interface to the vehicle ECU /\nCAN network. J12 carries CANH, CANL, and CAN_GND. Termination is populated only\nwhen the BMU is an end node.\n\n4. GPIO\nReserved GPIO signals and SHUTDOWN are kept for future expansion and shutdown/safety integration.\n\nRecommended test points:\n+12V-+32V, VIN_PROTECTED, +5V, +3V3, GND, \nCAN_TX, CAN_RX, CAN_STBY, CANH, CANL.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 34.036 144.018 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2.032 2.032)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "d92171e3-4207-439c-8e4d-3e2560cdbd94")
	)
	(text "12V → 5V → 3.3V"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 317.5 100.584 0)
